choices.text: There is a square grid of size $n \times n$. Some cells are colored in black, all others are colored in white. In one operation you can select some rectangle and color all its cells in white. It costs $\min(h, w)$ to color a rectangle of size $h \times w$. You are to make all cells white for minimum total cost. The square is large, so we give it to you in a compressed way. The set of black cells is the union of $m$ rectangles.
